The foreman's attitude is really what made me write this review. He's so damn uptight and snaps at his lovely staff all the time. Seeing his staff getting scolded by him really ruins the nice morning atmosphere. For example this morning I asked him if we could get the change after we got the check from our waitress and I didn't see her around to ask her directly. Stomach-churinging conditions. When I went here (2014), I found it to be the filthiest, grimiest, most run-down establishment in the city. Everything from the caked-up slimy mayo and dressing bottles, to the patched up booths with tape and glue peeling away. The railings had grime a penny thick, and the floor looked like a playground after the Fourth of July. The windows were cloudy with schmutz. The food was not very good. I have absolutely no idea how this restaurant not only continues to exist but somehow garners a rating higher than the best diners in the city. I suspect some shadiness, for this place to dodge the health department, and find happy customers to post. Don't go even if you're blind.

To start with, I consider myself an easy person to please.  I rate places 4 to 5 star that others might rate 3 or less.  I try to see the things that are important and ignore the things that aren't.  Broadway did not impress.  Any 2 of the things that went wrong I would have overlooked (had their only been 2 issues) but you stack 9 problems on top of each other and I give a bad review.  1. Had to wait at the door for a seat.  The could have offered to seat me at the bar (which had 6+ open sets) 2. The glass of orange juice had butter on the outside.  Makes me wonder how clean the inside was. 3. Water did not ask me how I wanted my potatoes (I ordered steak an eggs which comes with potatoes) 4. The water did not come with ice.  I personally don't care but it's unprofessional. 5. The food.  When it came, I was not impressed with how they just threw it on the plate.  The steak was very unevenly cooked, I assume it was because the grill was to hot.  It was also tasteless and did not come with a bottle of steak sauce.  It also seemed low quality. 6. The eggs and potatoes were also tasteless.  The potatoes were sloppily cooked. 7. The price seemed a little high then if I had gotten good food. 8. I placed my debit card on top of the bill and about 20 minutes later the waiter stopped by my table to tell me it was cash only. 9. When I actually went to the register to pay in cash, they gave me 3 dollars less change back then they should have and I had to ask for the difference.

Very friendly, pretty solid breakfast for Saturday at average prices

My husband and I eat here every single weekend. It's become our weekend breakfast place after stumbling upon it one weekend. I usually order the French toast with bacon, but I've also had the omelets, home fries and pancakes. Everything I've eaten is pretty much awesome diner food. The bacon is some of the best you'll have in your life. You even get a tiny orange juice with your breakfast. The place is small, so weekends can be crowded, but usually the wait isn't too bad. I recommend Broadway Restaurant whole heartedly to anyone looking for an amazing diner experience.
This is my favorite restaurant in New York. There are many diners like it, but it is the best.
